Hi Palvannan,

The time mismatch cis probably because your server's time is set to New York, and the client is probably located in India, hence the 9.5 hours difference between the two.
Because the server time can differ from the client time, we always recommend checking the client's time when viewing the logs.

The 5.9.4.1 server version is a maintenance one, it only has small fixes and improvements, so we don't have a fix list for it, but we always recommend using the latest server and client.

Best regards,

The time mismatch cis probably because your server's time is set to New York, and the client is probably located in India, hence the 9.5 hours difference between the two.
Because the server time can differ from the client time, we always recommend checking the client's time when viewing the logs.

The 5.9.4.1 server version is a maintenance one, it only has small fixes and improvements, so we don't have a fix list for it, but we always recommend using the latest server and client.

Hi Palvannan,

The time mismatch cis probably because your server's time is set to New York, and the client is probably located in India, hence the 9.5 hours difference between the two.
Because the server time can differ from the client time, we always recommend checking the client's time when viewing the logs.

The 5.9.4.1 server version is a maintenance one, it only has small fixes and improvements, so we don't have a fix list for it, but we always recommend using the latest server and client.

Best regards,

The time mismatch cis probably because your server's time is set to New York, and the client is probably located in India, hence the 9.5 hours difference between the two.
Because the server time can differ from the client time, we always recommend checking the client's time when viewing the logs.

The 5.9.4.1 server version is a maintenance one, it only has small fixes and improvements, so we don't have a fix list for it, but we always recommend using the latest server and client.

Hi Palvannan,

The time mismatch cis probably because your server's time is set to New York, and the client is probably located in India, hence the 9.5 hours difference between the two.
Because the server time can differ from the client time, we always recommend checking the client's time when viewing the logs.

The 5.9.4.1 server version is a maintenance one, it only has small fixes and improvements, so we don't have a fix list for it, but we always recommend using the latest server and client.

Best regards,

Hi Palvannan,

The time mismatch cis probably because your server's time is set to New York, and the client is probably located in India, hence the 9.5 hours difference between the two.
Because the server time can differ from the client time, we always recommend checking the client's time when viewing the logs.

The 5.9.4.1 server version is a maintenance one, it only has small fixes and improvements, so we don't have a fix list for it, but we always recommend using the latest server and client.

Best regards,
